          regulations (the “Law”), we make this privacy notice available to you
          so that you know the characteristics of the use that will be given to
          your personal data.
        </p>

        <h2>Personal data processed</h2>
        <p>
          Zillow may process the following personal data of candidates who are
          part of the recruitment and selection processes:
        </p>
        <br />
        <ul>
          <li>
            Identification data. Full name, age, sex, date of birth, place of
            birth, nationality, Federal Taxpayers Registry (R.F.C.), Unique Key
            of Population Registry (C.U.R.P.), official identification, marital
            status, image, signature and if applicable, immigration status.
          </li>
          <li>
            Contact information. Complete address, e-mail, mobile and/or
            landline telephone number.
          </li>
          <li>
            Employment data. Work history, curriculum vitae, current position,
            work permit.
          </li>
          <li>
            Academic data. Academic history, certificates of studies,
            professional license and other proof of studies, language skills,
            schooling.
          </li>
          <li>
            Personal and work references. Information provided to us by third
            parties from whom you have provided us with reference information
          </li>
          <li>
            Data related to your abilities, skills, aptitudes and personality.
            This information is the result of tests or exercises conducted
            during the recruitment and selection process, as well as the
            interviews carried out.
          </li>
          <li>
            Economic or patrimonial data. Information resulting from the
            socioeconomic studies carried out during the last stage of the
            recruitment and selection process; current salary and desired
            salary.
          </li>

          <p>We will not collect data considered sensitive by law.</p>

          <p>
            We may ask you to show us documentation related to the personal data
            you provide us, and to provide us with a simple copy of it. We may
            also corroborate such information in publicly available sources.
          </p>

          <p>
            During the process we may also collect personal data from third
            parties, for the purpose of obtaining personal and employment
            references of the candidates. These personal data are provided by
            the candidates and include:
          </p>

          <li>
            Identification data (full name), contact data (e-mail, telephone
            number) and, if applicable, employment data (company and position)
            of third parties designated by the candidate to obtain personal and
            employment references.
          </li>
          <p>
            The candidate must ensure that he/she has the prior authorization of
            any third parties of whom he/she provides us with personal data.
          </p>
        </ul>

        <h2>Purposes of processing personal data</h2>
        <p>
          The personal data we collect from you, as a candidate, may be used for
          the following necessary purposes:
        </p>
        <br />

        <ul>
          <li>
            To evaluate your profile and consider you for a recruitment and
            selection process.
          </li>
          <li>To contact you and, if necessary, to keep in touch with you.</li>
          <li>To allow you access to our facilities.</li>
          <li>
            To carry out the investigations, evaluations and in general all the
            steps that may be necessary during the recruitment and selection
            process.
          </li>
          <li>To request personal and work references.</li>
          <li>To compile candidate files.</li>
          <li>
            To make decisions regarding the recruitment and selection process.
          </li>
          <li>To conduct interviews.</li>
          <li>If applicable, to establish the job offer</li>
          <li>
            To ensure our safety, that of other candidates, personnel working in
            our offices and third parties who visit us.
          </li>
          <li>
            To comply with legal obligations and requirements of competent
            authorities.
          </li>
          <li>
            In the event of a dispute, to defend Zillow’s rights and interests,
            including before the competent authorities.
          </li>
          <li>To carry out the transfers indicated below.</li>
          <p>
            We may also process your personal data for the following voluntary
            purposes, which you may object to at any time by following the
            procedure set forth below:
          </p>
          <li>
            In the event that you are not selected to fill the job vacancy for
            which you applied, we may retain your personal data for up to one
            year in order to consider you for future recruitment and selection
            processes at Zillow.
          </li>
          <li>
            In the event that you are not selected to fill the job vacancy for
            which you applied, we may conduct resume exchanges with other
            companies within the same Zillow corporate group.
          </li>

          <p>
            Your personal data may be transferred to the following third
            parties, for the purposes set below:
          </p>
        </ul>
